5. And it is Ordered, &c. That if any Swine, belonging to either English or Indians, do there annoy or trespass such as there Fish as abovesaid, in the Mackrel seasons;
                        Trespass by Swine
                      it shall be lawful for any to make seizure of such Swine, paying the one half of the value of such Swine to the said Baily or his Deputy for the Colonies use.

